<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-02-17T12:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-02-17T12:30:00-05:00" n="677" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">810.796/5: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-02-17T13:00:00-04:30"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            17, 1928—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 7
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>5. Please see confidential letter from transportation division,
                                Department of Commerce, to the commercial attaché in Caracas January
                                    12.<note n="15" xml:id="d677fn15">Not printed; copy was
                                    transmitted to the Department in despatch No. 1497, Mar. 6,
                                    1928, from the Chargé in Venezuela (file No. 810.796/7).</note>
                                Does the Department desire the Legation to make discreet inquiries
                                regarding the Government’s attitude towards the proposed air
                                line?</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>